  stimulus_text = 'The narrator of this passage is a member of a royal family who is being groomed for a position of power. He describes the process of learning about his future role by observing and interacting with others. He is taught to be polite and deferential to those in positions of authority, but also to be aware of the complexities of human relationships. In particular, he learns that those who seem to be most powerful often operate in the shadows, and that it is important to be able to read the subtle signs of power and influence.  It is important for him to understand that power is not always what it seems, and that those who seem to be the most powerful often operate in the shadows, and that it is important to be able to read the subtle signs of power and influence. What is the most important lesson that the narrator is learning?',
